Explain a bit further wat u mean

Generally, I feel, prayer is as strong as your love for a person. A prayer, for example, for the soul of your grandma, girlfriend, or best buddy will be far more powerful than a prayer for the uncle of someone you know nothing about. A real name is also needed for prayer.
This should not mean that it is a bad idea to pray for random people that ask for it, but that it is better to pray for your irl loved ones and people you have established a true connection with.

In cases in which I feel strong empathy for the person I always say a prayer. If it is a heartfelt requests and hits me in my feelings, then I can connect with the person. A prayer is not just saying things in your mind, it should be a literal spiritual bridge, a connection.
I have been told that prayer is what connects the three Persons of the Trinity, but this is a topic way too deep for twitter
